        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 29 at 4:39PM MDT by NWS Missoula MT</headline>
        <description>At 438 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lolo, or 7 miles southwest of Missoula, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Torrential rainfall and Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible. Torrential
rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding.

Locations impacted include...
southern portions of Missoula and Lolo.

This includes Highway 93 S between mile markers 81 and 88.
</description>
        <instruction>Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.

This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
